# Data Model

## Core principle

- **Contact** = the real client/person in the CRM
- **ContactIdentity** = channel-specific identity (WhatsApp phone, Instagram user id, manual phone)
- **Never** auto-merge WhatsApp and Instagram users by display name alone

## Tenant scoping

- `workspace_id` on every tenant-owned table
- All reads/writes scoped to current workspace
- RLS policies enforce isolation at the database layer

## Idempotency

- External message IDs must be unique per provider/workspace to prevent duplicate webhook processing
- Use unique constraints on `(workspace_id, provider, external_message_id)` or equivalent

## Expected domain models

Workspace, User/Profile, Contact, ContactIdentity, Conversation, Message, Note, Appointment, SessionPackage, SessionUsage, FollowUpTask, ReplyTemplate

> Docs may use `TreatmentPackage` — treat as alias for `SessionPackage` until renamed in schema.

## Identity matching

- Match inbound events on verified channel identifiers (phone, external user id), not name similarity
- Suggested merges require human confirmation + audit log

